Get Real-Time Weather Updates with Just a Few Lines of Code! üå¶Ô∏è

This lightweight Python script allows you to fetch real-time weather data for any location worldwide. Perfect for IoT projects, smart home systems, travel apps, or automation scripts, this tool connects to a weather API (like OpenWeatherMap) and returns key details such as temperature, humidity, wind speed, and forecasts.
import requests
city = input("Enter the city name: ")
print(city)
url='https://wttr.in/{}'.format(city)
req=requests.get(url)
print('Displying Weather Reports for' + city)
print(req.text)
